I use it to install MySQL with some non default values. I&#x27;m not that good with bash and install scripts and expect was the only way around some issues I was having.<p><pre><code>  secure_mysql_script=$(expect -c &#x27;
  spawn sudo mysql_secure_installation
  expect &quot;Enter current password for root (enter for none):&quot;
  send &quot;\r&quot;
  expect &quot;Change the root password?&quot;
  send &quot;n\r&quot;
  expect &quot;Remove anonymous users?&quot;
  send &quot;y\r&quot;
  expect &quot;Disallow root login remotely?&quot;
  send &quot;y\r&quot;
  expect &quot;Remove test database and access to it?&quot;
  send &quot;y\r&quot;
  expect &quot;Reload privilege tables now?&quot;
  send &quot;y\r&quot;
  expect eof
  &#x27;)
  echo &quot;$secure_mysql_script&quot;</code></pre>
